<ns4181:section xmlns:ns4181="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.qualityAttributes.modifiability.complexityReduction">

  <ns4182:title xmlns:ns4182="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Complexity reduction</ns4182:title>
  <ns4183:para xmlns:ns4183="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    Complexity is one of the biggest contributors to the cost of change. Simpler systems
    usually absorb changes to the requirements more readily than complex systems.
  </ns4183:para>
  
  <ns4184:section xmlns:ns4184="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4185:title xmlns:ns4185="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Minimize component complexity</ns4185:title>
    <ns4186:para xmlns:ns4186="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      This includes implementation complexities like
      <ns4187:itemizedlist xmlns:ns4187="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4188:listitem xmlns:ns4188="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4189:para xmlns:ns4189="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          the complexity of the algorithms realizing the work flows,
        </ns4189:para></ns4188:listitem>
        <ns4190:listitem xmlns:ns4190="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns4191:para xmlns:ns4191="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          and structural complexity like the complexity of the data structures used.
        </ns4191:para></ns4190:listitem>
      </ns4187:itemizedlist>
    </ns4186:para>
  </ns4184:section>
  
  <ns4192:section xmlns:ns4192="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns4193:title xmlns:ns4193="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Minimize dependency between classes</ns4193:title>
    <ns4194:para xmlns:ns4194="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      If there is a strong dependency between classes, it is difficult to modify any of these
      without at least checking all the others. In general modifiability is improved by
      ensuring that one only adds those dependencies and associations which are
      essential for realizing the system use cases.
    </ns4194:para>
    <ns4195:section xmlns:ns4195="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns4196:title xmlns:ns4196="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Reducing dependencies via the mediator pattern</ns4196:title>
      <ns4197:para xmlns:ns4197="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        At times one requires navigability between a group of components which are otherwise
        unrelated. In such cases it is often a good idea to not introduce direct dependencies
        between these components but to facilitate navigation via a mediator.
      </ns4197:para>
    </ns4195:section>
    
  </ns4192:section>
  
</ns4181:section>